base_prompt:
Scientific illustration in the Organic School tradition, rendered as if by a Yeller Quarry field naturalist.

SUBJECT: {creature_name}
- Depicted in {pose}
- Key features visible: {features}

MATERIALS AND COLORS:
- Line work: Variable flowing lines using Toadpipe Bile ink
- Paper: Quarry-sourced rough paper (#DEB887)
- Primary color: {primary_hex} ({material_name})
- Secondary color: {secondary_hex}
- Accents: {accent_description}

STYLE:
- Living mathematics aesthetic
- Flowing curves suggesting creature movement
- Variable line weight emphasizes {emphasized_features}
- Quick-sketch authenticity over polished finish

NOTATION:
- Species name in field script at lower left
- Scale reference: {scale_reference}

COMPOSITION:
- {view_angle} view
- Creature fills frame with breathing room
- Background suggests habitat without overwhelming subject

EXCLUDE: Dramatic lighting, photorealism, decorative borders, anatomical impossibilities
